<sect2 id="function_overloading">
<title>Dynamic Function Overloading</title>

<para>
A symbol in ATS can be overloaded with multiple (dynamic)
functions. The following syntax introduces a symbol of the name
<code>foo</code> for overloading:
</para>

<informalexample><programlisting><![CDATA[symintr foo // symbol introduction for overloading
]]></programlisting></informalexample>


<para>
Suppose that <code>foo1</code>, <code>foo2</code> and <code>foo3</code> are
names of three functions in ATS. Then we can overload <code>foo</code> with
these three functions as follows:
</para>

<informalexample><programlisting><![CDATA[overload foo with foo1
overload foo with foo2
overload foo with foo3
]]></programlisting></informalexample>


<para>
An overloaded function symbol is resolved according to the number of
arguments it takes and, if needed, the types of these arguments.

</para>

</sect2><!--id="function_overloading"-->

</sect1><!--id="overloading"-->

